									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I actually really like this, particularly with the customised silhouette idea. However. Penguin covers are colour-coded. According to Wikipedia:<br />
&#8220;&#8230;orange and white for general fiction, green and white for crime fiction, cerise and white for travel and adventure, dark blue and white for biographies, yellow and white for miscellaneous, red and white for drama; and the rarer purple and white for essays and belles lettres and grey and white for world affairs.&#8221;</p>
<p>I am not a huge fan of orange. I vote yellow, or that we invent a new shade for the category &#8220;micfic&#8221;.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

